We lost by three runs

11:18.761 --> 11:21.556
and had a barbecue, Mel.

11:22.349 --> 11:24.392
And it wasn't on my watch.

11:24.434 --> 11:26.520
So, can I see the

11:24.434 --> 11:26.520
underwear dance?

11:26.561 --> 11:28.771
Yeah, you'd like that,

11:26.561 --> 11:28.771
wouldn't you?

11:28.813 --> 11:30.106
Would you?

11:30.148 --> 11:31.816
Slow down, we haven't

11:30.148 --> 11:31.816
even kissed yet.

11:31.858 --> 11:33.193
Malcolm, let's go,

11:31.858 --> 11:33.193
we got to get

11:33.234 --> 11:34.653
to your zit doctor

11:33.234 --> 11:34.653
before 5:00.

11:34.693 --> 11:36.655
Mom!

11:34.693 --> 11:36.655
What?

11:36.695 --> 11:38.739
Your friend doesn't care

11:36.695 --> 11:38.739
about that.

11:38.781 --> 11:42.701
Look at  her  face-- she probably

11:38.781 --> 11:42.701
goes to the same doctor.

11:43.286 --> 11:45.788
(door opens)

11:45.830 --> 11:47.374
Hello, Mother.

11:47.415 --> 11:49.750
Hey, Francis. I thought

11:47.415 --> 11:49.750
you left this morning.

11:49.792 --> 11:50.960
I did.

11:51.002 --> 11:52.753
I got halfway home

11:52.795 --> 11:53.754
when I suddenly

11:53.796 --> 11:54.797
remembered the time

11:54.839 --> 11:56.257
when I was three years old

11:56.299 --> 11:59.010
and you were sick--

11:56.299 --> 11:59.010
or so you said--

11:59.052 --> 12:00.345
and couldn't drive me

12:00.387 --> 12:02.222
to Donnie Dinesco's

12:00.387 --> 12:02.222
birthday party.

12:02.263 --> 12:06.767
So I rode  this  tricycle

12:02.263 --> 12:06.767
two miles in the pouring rain

12:06.809 --> 12:08.144
just to get there.

12:08.186 --> 12:10.188
Lazy? I think not.

12:10.230 --> 12:11.231
Now, I am not leaving

12:11.272 --> 12:13.191
until you apologize.

12:13.233 --> 12:15.193
All you want is an

12:13.233 --> 12:15.193
apology? That's it?

12:15.235 --> 12:17.278
Well, you should've

12:15.235 --> 12:17.278
said so a week ago.

12:17.320 --> 12:18.279
But...

12:18.321 --> 12:20.031
I'm hereby officially sorry.

12:20.073 --> 12:23.451
Okay?

12:20.073 --> 12:23.451
No! Not okay!

12:23.493 --> 12:24.952
That is not an apology.

12:24.994 --> 12:27.788
That's just one of those

12:24.994 --> 12:27.788
cleverly designed apologies

12:27.830 --> 12:30.041
that sounds like an apology

12:27.830 --> 12:30.041
but isn't one.

12:30.083 --> 12:32.793
Now you have to apologize

12:30.083 --> 12:32.793
for apologizing.

12:32.835 --> 12:34.170
And then apologize!

12:34.212 --> 12:35.796
You know what

12:34.212 --> 12:35.796
your problem is?

12:35.838 --> 12:38.091
You know why you can't

12:35.838 --> 12:38.091
accept my apology?

12:38.132 --> 12:41.302
Because you just can't

12:38.132 --> 12:41.302
stand to be happy!

12:41.344 --> 12:42.512
What?!

12:42.554 --> 12:44.013
You have an addiction

12:42.554 --> 12:44.013
to trouble.

12:44.055 --> 12:46.725
You need to have chaos in

12:44.055 --> 12:46.725
your life-- you always have.

12:46.765 --> 12:47.726
I mean, look at you.

12:47.766 --> 12:50.103
You have a great job,

12:50.144 --> 12:53.440
a nice home, a wife,

12:50.144 --> 12:53.440
and you can't stand it.

12:53.481 --> 12:54.815
You have to

12:53.481 --> 12:54.815
come back here

12:54.857 --> 12:56.317
and pick a fight

12:54.857 --> 12:56.317
with your mother.

12:56.359 --> 12:57.527
That's not true.

12:57.569 --> 12:58.861
I came back here because

12:58.903 --> 13:01.030
you've destroyed

12:58.903 --> 13:01.030
any chance any of us

13:01.072 --> 13:02.616
ever had for happiness.

13:02.657 --> 13:04.409
Tell her, Malcolm.

13:04.451 --> 13:06.077
Tell her what a horrible

13:04.451 --> 13:06.077
mother she is.

13:06.119 --> 13:07.828
He's right--

13:06.119 --> 13:07.828
you insinuate yourself

13:07.870 --> 13:09.830
into every part of our lives,

13:07.870 --> 13:09.830
just to make sure

13:09.872 --> 13:11.874
there's no place

13:09.872 --> 13:11.874
we're not miserable.

13:11.916 --> 13:13.042
Well, you're

13:11.916 --> 13:13.042
not gonna

13:13.084 --> 13:14.419
turn me into

13:13.084 --> 13:14.419
a drooling infant

13:14.461 --> 13:15.420
like you did Francis.

13:15.462 --> 13:16.837
Yeah! What?

13:16.879 --> 13:18.757
I'm quitting

13:16.879 --> 13:18.757
the softball team.

13:18.797 --> 13:20.883
You are doing no such thing,

13:18.797 --> 13:20.883
Malcolm.

13:20.925 --> 13:23.886
You had a chance to quit,

13:20.925 --> 13:23.886
but now we have a game.

13:23.928 --> 13:25.472
You made a commitment to a team,

13:25.513 --> 13:27.265
and other people

13:25.513 --> 13:27.265
are counting on you.

13:27.307 --> 13:28.767
You can't force me to play.

13:28.807 --> 13:30.851
No, but I can confiscate

13:28.807 --> 13:30.851
your paychecks.

13:30.893 --> 13:33.854
You're gonna take away money

13:30.893 --> 13:33.854
that's legally mine

13:33.896 --> 13:35.273
for a game of softball?

13:35.315 --> 13:37.942
I don't know. Am I?

13:38.777 --> 13:41.028
You are pure evil.

13:41.070 --> 13:44.282
How do you sleep

13:41.070 --> 13:44.282
at night?

13:44.324 --> 13:46.785
Hal, will you please

13:44.324 --> 13:46.785
talk to the boys?

13:46.825 --> 13:49.120
Not now, Lois, I have

13:46.825 --> 13:49.120
way too much on my mind.

13:49.162 --> 13:50.371
Like what?

13:50.413 --> 13:52.749
I think I'm an

13:50.413 --> 13:52.749
international spy,

13:52.791 --> 13:54.501
and I don't even know

13:52.791 --> 13:54.501
which side I'm on.

13:54.542 --> 13:58.254
I could be a super-villain

13:54.542 --> 13:58.254
and not even know it.

13:58.296 --> 14:01.591
You can just say

13:58.296 --> 14:01.591
you don't want to help me, Hal.

14:02.759 --> 14:04.385
You look very handsome

14:02.759 --> 14:04.385
in your uniform.

14:04.427 --> 14:07.514
I wish you would've let me

14:04.427 --> 14:07.514
take it in around the arms.

14:08.389 --> 14:10.600
Well, good news for you, Lois.

14:10.642 --> 14:11.892
Our right fielder

14:11.934 --> 14:13.394
was screwing around

14:11.934 --> 14:13.394
with a price gun,

14:13.436 --> 14:14.895
took a sticker to the eye.

14:14.937 --> 14:15.896
We're a player short.

14:15.938 --> 14:17.482
We have to forfeit.

14:17.524 --> 14:18.525
Yes!

14:18.983 --> 14:19.900
All right! Amen!

14:19.942 --> 14:20.985
Well, too bad.

14:21.027 --> 14:24.071
Course, the

14:21.027 --> 14:24.071
real losers...

14:24.113 --> 14:26.616
the fans.

14:26.658 --> 14:28.868
Not today, Tonto.

14:29.869 --> 14:31.078
That's just silly.

14:31.120 --> 14:32.789
We're all here,

14:31.120 --> 14:32.789
we're all in uniform,

14:32.831 --> 14:33.914
everyone wants to play.

14:33.956 --> 14:36.125
Malcolm, go be

14:33.956 --> 14:36.125
on Mel's team.

14:36.167 --> 14:36.917
What?

14:36.959 --> 14:38.336
Oh, yeah, big favor.

14:38.378 --> 14:39.796
No, no, no, no,

14:38.378 --> 14:39.796
no, his game

14:39.838 --> 14:41.214
has really improved.

14:39.838 --> 14:41.214
Hasn't it, honey?

14:41.255 --> 14:44.091
After all that stuff about

14:41.255 --> 14:44.091
my commitment to this team,

14:44.133 --> 14:46.177
you could just decide

14:44.133 --> 14:46.177
to give me away?

14:46.219 --> 14:49.514
Malcolm, everybody's nervous

14:46.219 --> 14:49.514
about making new friends.

14:49.556 --> 14:52.851
Just be yourself.

14:49.556 --> 14:52.851
They'll like you fine.

14:57.438 --> 14:59.940
I'm gonna hit this ball

14:57.438 --> 14:59.940
so far out of the park,

14:59.982 --> 15:01.568
my mom's gonna wish she never...

15:01.609 --> 15:03.778
Wait, what do I do

15:01.609 --> 15:03.778
with my hips again?

15:03.820 --> 15:05.488
Strike one!

15:03.820 --> 15:05.488
What?

15:06.155 --> 15:08.032
Okay, it'll be okay.

15:08.074 --> 15:09.950
Just stop thinking.

15:09.992 --> 15:11.911
You can do it, honey.

15:12.829 --> 15:13.954
Strike two!

15:13.996 --> 15:15.790
Look, just don't talk

15:13.996 --> 15:15.790
to me, okay?!

15:15.832 --> 15:17.751
Just pitch the ball!

15:17.792 --> 15:19.001
I can't believe

15:17.792 --> 15:19.001
she's doing this.

15:19.043 --> 15:20.961
I just hate it

15:19.043 --> 15:20.961
when she treats me like this

15:21.003 --> 15:22.171
in front of everyone.

15:21.003 --> 15:22.171
It's so...

15:22.213 --> 15:24.173
Strike three!

15:26.885 --> 15:28.595
(cell phone ringing)

15:26.885 --> 15:28.595
FRANCIS:  Hello?

15:28.636 --> 15:30.054
No, honey bun, I'm still here.

15:30.096 --> 15:32.181
I have a few more things

15:30.096 --> 15:32.181
to straighten out

15:32.223 --> 15:33.974
before I can leave,

15:32.223 --> 15:33.974
but I promise

15:34.016 --> 15:35.976
that we will celebrate

15:34.016 --> 15:35.976
our anniversary

15:36.018 --> 15:38.062
as soon as I get home.

15:38.104 --> 15:40.147
Right, if you're still there.

15:40.189 --> 15:42.066
(knocking)

15:42.108 --> 15:44.277
Did Reese and Dewey

15:42.108 --> 15:44.277
leave yet?

